text: Good evening, I'd like to call this regular council meeting to order. It is Tuesday, November 18th, 2025. The time is 7:00 PM.
Could I have a motion to approve the agenda as presented?
So moved.
Seconded.
All those in favour? Carried unanimously. Moving on to public participation.
We have three delegations this evening regarding traffic concerns on Helmcken Road. I'd like to invite our first speaker to the podium.
Thank you, Mayor Screech and members of council. I live on Helmcken Road near View Royal Elementary and I'm here to talk about the dangerous speeding situation we've been dealing with for years.
During school drop-off and pick-up times, vehicles regularly exceed the 30 kilometer per hour speed limit. We've clocked cars going 60 to 70 kilometers per hour right past the school.
I'd like to move that staff be directed to conduct a traffic study on Helmcken Road between View Royal Avenue and Beaumont Avenue.
I'll second that motion.
We now move to item 8.1, Tree Protection Bylaw Number 1160. This bylaw is before council for second and third readings following the public hearing held on October 21st.
I have concerns about the 20 centimeter diameter threshold. That captures a lot of relatively young trees that homeowners should be able to manage on their own property without a permit process.

I agree with Councillor Kowalewich. This bylaw as written is too restrictive. We need to balance environmental protection with property rights. I'd suggest we increase the threshold to at least 30 centimeters.

I understand the concerns but we've heard from many residents who support strong tree protection. The arborist report recommended the 20 centimeter threshold. However, I could support a compromise at 30 centimeters.
Moving on to item 9.1, the annual financial report. I'll ask our Director of Finance to present.

Thank you, Mayor. I'm pleased to report that the Town ended the 2024-2025 fiscal year with a surplus of approximately $142,000. This was primarily due to lower than anticipated spending on road maintenance contracts.
What is the current balance in our infrastructure reserve fund?
The infrastructure reserve currently stands at $3.2 million, which is approximately 85% of our target level.
I'd like to move that the Annual Financial Report for fiscal year 2024-2025 be received for information.
Seconded.
